CROSS-REPO WORK LOG: may_minihttp follow-up
Date: 2026-04-18
========================================
Context:
  - PR #24 (feat/response-header-owned-values) still in review upstream.
  - Local analysis of src/request.rs decode() identified a redundant
    O(n) \r\n\r\n pre-scan that duplicates httparse's own Status::Partial
    behaviour.
  - Empirical probe across 15 truncation + malformed-input cases
    confirmed: truncation yields Partial, malformed bytes yield
    Token/HeaderName/Version. No case where the pre-scan converted a
    Token error into a Partial.

Action:
  - Branched fix/remove-redundant-preparse-check from
    feat/response-header-owned-values (stacks on PR #24).
  - Removed the pre-scan in src/request.rs decode(), replaced with a
    doc comment explaining why it is redundant.
  - Local CI mirror green: clippy (default + --examples) + fmt + cargo
    test (only pre-existing perf-threshold flake on
    request_parsing::performance::benchmark_completion_check, fires
    identically on parent under full-suite concurrent load; measures a
    test-local helper, not touched code).
  - Committer: Charles Sibbald <casibbald@gmail.com>
    (no Cursor co-author trailer — per CLI-first / client-security rule)
  - Commit: 8095cd2 perf(request): remove redundant \r\n\r\n pre-scan
    before httparse (src/request.rs +15 -7)
  - Pushed: origin/fix/remove-redundant-preparse-check
    https://github.com/microscaler/may_minihttp/pull/new/fix/remove-redundant-preparse-check

Pending:
  - Await #24 review; when merged, rebase this branch onto master and
    forward as upstream PR to Xudong-Huang/may_minihttp.
  - BRRTRouter Phase 2.3 (double path alloc), header-value intern,
    write_json_error body-formatting, Goose v2 scenario matrix still on
    PRD roadmap (docs/PRD_HOT_PATH_V2_STABILITY_AND_PERF.md).
