ADDENDUM 2026-04-18: may_minihttp pre-scan removal REVERTED
  - Commit 8095cd2 (pre-scan removal) regressed BRRTRouter's 403
    response tests. httparse returns Err(Token) on stale body bytes
    from keep-alive (e.g. client sent more body than Content-Length,
    leaving leftover bytes for next decode). Pre-scan was silently
    masking this — removing it surfaces 500+connection-reset before
    the 403 response is written.
  - Rebased integration/microscaler-fork to drop 8095cd2. New tip
    9175f9a. Force-pushed. BRRTRouter 299 lib tests: all green.
  - Committed BRRTRouter pin change as 36379d0 on pre_BFF_work,
    pushed.
  - Still broken: fix/remove-redundant-preparse-check branch on
    may_minihttp still has 8095cd2 + its PR description. User needs
    to decide: rebase the branch to drop the bad commit, rename it,
    or delete entirely.
========================================


ADDENDUM 2026-04-18: BRRTRouter Phase R rerun — +15.6 % throughput confirmed
  - 3 × 2000u × 600s Goose bench against pet_store :8091. First attempt
    hit SIGABRT ~4 min into run 1 from hot-path warn! spam
    (router/core "Slow route matching" per-request, memory middleware
    "High memory growth" every 10s, may odd-stack println per
    coroutine). Demoted all three to debug!/gated, rebuilt, reran.
  - Results: 76,626 / 75,525 / 78,430 req/s (mean 76,860, ±1.9 %),
    0 % connection errors, avg 25.23 ms, median 22.7 ms.
  - vs Phase 0.3+2.1 arcswap baseline (66,484 / 29.21 ms): +15.6 %
    throughput, -13.6 % avg latency, -11.5 % p50.
  - PRD §Phase R.1 "thermal drift" hypothesis disproven — cause was
    SIGABRT from log-pipeline saturation under load, not scheduler
    noise. PRD updated to 1.7 with correct diagnosis.
  - Commit b1fc30b pushed to pre_BFF_work.
  - Harness noise floor dropped from ±10 % → ±1.9 % on same hardware
    just from hot-path log hygiene. "Laptop too noisy" argument for
    Phase 6 Goose rewrite was overstated.
